,"year":-1053},{"id":"recbBF1rzVdtRJxUq","ref":"2Sam.1.2","text":"It came even to pass on the third day, that, behold, a man came out of the camp from Saul with his clothes rent, and earth upon his head: and so it was, when he came to David, that he fell to the earth, and did obeisance.","year":-1053},{"id":"recRZbisuJMXS9tNR","ref":"2Sam.1.3","text":"And David said unto him, From whence comest thou? And he said unto him, Out of the camp of Israel am I escaped.","year":-1053},{"id":"recQY7arzohiKYAMT","ref":"2Sam.1.4","text":"And David said unto him, How went the matter? I pray thee, tell me. And he answered, That the people are fled from the battle, and many of the people also are fallen and dead; and Saul and Jonathan his son are dead also.","year":-1053},{"id":"rec4uXhwtWTJ4UT7d","ref":"2Sam.1.5","text":"And David said unto the young man that told him, How knowest thou that Saul and Jonathan his son be dead?","year":-1053},{"id":"recTmRsUTUQ0ahkqK","ref":"2Sam.1.6","text":"And the young man that told him said, As I happened by chance upon mount Gilboa, behold, Saul leaned upon his spear; and, lo, the chariots and horsemen followed hard after him.","year":-1053}]}
